@PuccaNoodles I chose to depict trees like that because I live in Maine (so lots of trees everywhere) and these trees stood out from the comparatively boring green ones that were virtually everywhere else.  Im glad my mother sided with me when the teacher called her in to talk about it.

@PuccaNoodles My teacher got pissed because for the spring and summer trees I colored the leaves purple.  There were trees half a football field away from the windows that looked like the one pictured, but bigger.  We had like 6 giant crayons to use for this.pic.twitter.com/5pcGeDHzIc

@PuccaNoodles In kindergarten there was one time when we had a small coloring project where we had to depict the four seasons one normally gets in a temperate climate in the US.  Everyone drew four small, simple scenes, almost all of them depicting a tree and immediate surround area.
